OL,3,CFormer nuns and support worker
OL,4,Csentenced over historic abuse at
OL,5,Cchildren's homes
OL,7,FThe offences took place at two homes
OL,8,Fin Lasswade, Midlothian, and
OL,9,FKilmarnock, East Ayrshire, run by the
OL,10,FCatholic order, the Sisters of
OL,11,FNazareth, between the early 1970s and
OL,12,Fearly 1980s.
OL,14,FJurors were told how Buirds, of
OL,15,FWallsend, Tyne and Wear, had rubbed
OL,16,Furine-soaked bedding on children, and
OL,17,Fforced food and soap into their mouths.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/12
