OL,4,Csentenced over historic abuse at
OL,5,Cchildren's homes
OL,7,FMcElhinney, of Bishopbriggs, East
OL,8,FDunbartonshire, was made subject to a
OL,9,F12-month probation order and told to
OL,10,Fperform 240 hours of unpaid work, and
OL,11,Fgiven a nine-month curfew between the
OL,12,Fhours of 4pm and midnight.
OL,14,FKane, of Lasswade, was given a
OL,15,Fcommunity service order with a
OL,16,Frequirement to complete 150 hours of
OL,17,Funpaid work within nine months.
