OL,4,Csentenced over historic abuse at
OL,5,Cchildren's homes
OL,7,FFaith Currie, procurator fiscal for
OL,8,FLothian and Borders at the Crown
OL,9,FOffice and Procurator Fiscal Service,
OL,10,Fsaid: "Carol Buirds, Eileen McElhinney
OL,11,Fand Dorothy Kane were entrusted with
OL,12,Fthe care of vulnerable children, but
OL,13,Finstead they betrayed that trust and
OL,14,Finflicted lasting harm through their
OL,15,Fcriminal actions.
OL,17,F"It is now a matter of public record
OL,18,Fthat they gravely breached their duty
OL,19,Fof care while holding positions of
OL,20,Ftrust and authority at Nazareth House.
